Here's how simply our
Small-Package Dispatch
works:
Just take your small package to United's passenger
check-in counter at your airport. We'll give you a re-
ceipt and your package goes right with the passen-
gers' luggage. It can go on the next flight leaving 30
minutes or more after we accept it. Or on any later
flight you specify.
At its destination, your package moves with the pas-
sengers' luggage from the plane directly to the bag-
gage claim area. Just claim it like luggage. Fast? See
for yourself next time you have to rush a package.
Unique features:
Your package goes with the baggage on any pas-
senger flight or flights you specify.
We'll refund 50% for shipments not delivered on
flights specified, except if caused by weather, me-
chanical problems or exclusions named in the appli-
cable tariffs -"Acts of God," for instance.
The highlights:
One package per shipment-no lot shipments.
Maximum size: 90 inches total dimensions (length,
width and height)
• Maximum weight: 50 lbs. per shipment.
Airport to airport service-no pickup or delivery.
• Routings are all-United, either direct or on a con-
necting flight.
Check-in deadline: 30 minutes before scheduled
flight departure.
Available for pickup by consignee 30 minutes after
actual flight arrival.
Charges prepaid—no collect or C.O.D.
Flight connections handled just like checked
baggage.
Items not acceptable: flowers, vegetables, live ani-
mals, meat, and articles not acceptable under appli-
cable tariffs.
Declared value: $50 per shipment unless a higher
value is declared on the airbill, and an additional
charge paid. Maximum declarable value: $500.00.
Total liability limited to the least of one of the follow-
ing: value of shipment; value as declared; or amount
of any damage sustained.
